sections.History:
===[[Season 1]]===
[[Eddard Stark|Ned Stark]] is confined to the Black Cells following his [[Massacre in the Red Keep|arrest]]. He is visited twice by [[Varys]] who tries to convince him to confess to treason in order to prevent war and to save the lives of his daughters [[Sansa Stark|Sansa]] and [[Arya Stark|Arya]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Baelor]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===

After learning that [[Pycelle]] is an informant for Queen [[Cersei Lannister|Cersei]], [[Tyrion Lannister]] has his men [[Timett]] and [[Bronn]] cut off Pycelle's beard and throw him into one of the Black Cells.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[What is Dead May Never Die]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Not long afterwards Cersei sends [[Lancel Lannister|Lancel]] to demand that Tyrion have Pycelle freed. He agrees to let him go, given that he has made his point, but will not let him return to the [[Small Council]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Garden of Bones]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Tyrion is confined to the Black Cells after being [[Second Trial by combat of Tyrion Lannister|found guilty]] of the [[Purple Wedding|murder]] of his nephew King [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey]]. On the eve of his execution, [[Jaime Lannister|Jaime]] frees Tyrion, so he can escape to the [[Free Cities]]. Tyrion first uses the passages in the Red Keep to visit the [[Tower of the Hand]] and [[Assassination at the Tower of the Hand|confront and kill]] his [[Tywin Lannister|father]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
